    "Alikaniotis et al. (2016) utilize C &W embeddings to represent essays, aiming to capture semantic information before employing LSTM for essay scoring.",
    "In addition to training word embeddings on the target dataset, pre-trained word embeddings can also be utilized.",
    "These pre-trained word embeddings are trained on large datasets, such as Wikipedia and news data, and can be fine-tuned on the target dataset.",
    "Word2Vec is a software package that includes two algorithms: Continuous Bag-of-Words (CBOW) and Skip-gram (Mikolov et al. 2013).",
    "CBOW predicts a center word based on the surrounding context in terms of word vectors, while the skip-gram algorithm predicts the distribution of context words based on a center word."
